WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:11.040 --> 00:00:12.393
It was gone.

00:00:12.393 --> 00:00:13.703
 In a single morning,  

00:00:13.703 --> 00:00:16.527
more than&nbsp;$40 million had just disappeared

00:00:16.527 --> 00:00:18.984
from one of&nbsp;France's biggest banks. 

00:00:18.984 --> 00:00:21.101
When the police finally&nbsp;got into the vault,

00:00:21.101 --> 00:00:24.558
 it was obvious that this was no ordinary bank robbery.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:24.558 --> 00:00:26.982
Instead of breaking&nbsp;into the bank itself, 

00:00:26.982 --> 00:00:29.750
the thieves had tunneled&nbsp;all the way from the sewers

00:00:29.750 --> 00:00:32.857
and straight through&nbsp;the concrete walls of the vault. 

00:00:32.857 --> 00:00:33.680
When inside,&nbsp;

00:00:33.680 --> 00:00:36.096
they ransacked the safe deposit boxes, 

00:00:36.096 --> 00:00:38.664
taking&nbsp;gold, cash, and precious jewels 

00:00:38.664 --> 00:00:41.298
before vanishing back into the sewers.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:41.298 --> 00:00:45.373
 It's not every day that you&nbsp;suddenly decide to rob a bank,

00:00:45.373 --> 00:00:47.530
But in September&nbsp;1974&nbsp;

00:00:47.530 --> 00:00:51.283
that's exactly what happened to Albert Spaggiari. 

00:00:51.283 --> 00:00:54.261
He&nbsp;had just become a customer of the Société Générale

00:00:54.261 --> 00:00:57.546
and went to drop off some money into a&nbsp;safe deposit box. 

00:00:57.546 --> 00:00:58.880
When he was inside the vault,&nbsp;

00:00:58.880 --> 00:01:03.079
he noticed that there wasn't a single alarm in&nbsp;the entire vault. 

00:01:03.079 --> 00:01:04.480
To make sure he was correct,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:04.480 --> 00:01:08.430
the next day he placed an alarm clock 
inside&nbsp;his safe deposit box 

00:01:08.430 --> 00:01:10.832
and set it to go off at 1:00&nbsp;AM

00:01:10.832 --> 00:01:11.954
If there was an alarm

00:01:11.954 --> 00:01:14.833
surely the sound&nbsp;of his clock would trigger it. 

00:01:14.833 --> 00:01:15.600
That evening

00:01:15.600 --> 00:01:18.136
Albert waited in a bar across the street

00:01:18.136 --> 00:01:21.515
and&nbsp;when 1:00 AM arrived, nothing happened. 

00:01:21.515 --> 00:01:24.563
At&nbsp;&nbsp;this point, he knew he was going to rob the&nbsp;bank

00:01:24.563 --> 00:01:27.309
 but he still had no idea how. 

00:01:27.309 --> 00:01:30.173
Then,&nbsp;when he was scoping out the exterior of&nbsp;the bank, 

00:01:30.173 --> 00:01:32.274
he overheard a conversation.

00:01:52.640 --> 00:01:55.230
Suddenly, it clicked in Albert's head. 

00:01:55.230 --> 00:01:57.920
Nice&nbsp;used to have a river running through its center&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:57.920 --> 00:02:00.745
where many of the old sewer lines fed into. &nbsp;

00:02:00.745 --> 00:02:03.680
But&nbsp;after decades of building on top of the river

00:02:03.680 --> 00:02:06.350
this area was now completely underground

00:02:06.350 --> 00:02:10.307
and&nbsp;enormous tunnels had been built 
to handle the&nbsp;river during a flood.

00:02:10.307 --> 00:02:13.195
If one of these sewer&nbsp;tunnels went anywhere near the bank,

00:02:13.195 --> 00:02:16.220
it&nbsp;could allow Albert to dig his way into the vault&nbsp;

00:02:16.220 --> 00:02:18.254
without anyone noticing. 

00:02:18.254 --> 00:02:22.423
Albert managed to get his&nbsp;hands 
on blueprints of the city's sewer system.&nbsp;

00:02:22.423 --> 00:02:23.395
According to these, 

00:02:23.395 --> 00:02:25.718
there was a ramp underneath the convention center&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:25.718 --> 00:02:29.164
that led down into the&nbsp;city's main sewage tunnels.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:29.164 --> 00:02:29.664
From there,

00:02:29.664 --> 00:02:32.943
a service road inside the tunnel followed the old river

00:02:32.943 --> 00:02:35.267
&nbsp;until it reached the Masséna Plaza. 

00:02:35.267 --> 00:02:37.747
Then a smaller&nbsp;sewage tunnel broke off 

00:02:37.747 --> 00:02:42.609
and ran underneath the&nbsp;streets and crucially right past the bank. 

00:02:42.609 --> 00:02:45.000
Being&nbsp;the well-connected criminal that he was,

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:48.720
Albert&nbsp;quickly pulled together a team of around 20 men.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:48.720 --> 00:02:52.479
He had tunneling experts, plumbers, electricians,&nbsp;welders. 

00:02:52.479 --> 00:02:54.113
These guys were professionals, 

00:02:54.113 --> 00:02:57.059
and all they needed now was the equipment. 

00:02:57.059 --> 00:02:58.879
To be extra&nbsp;cautious

00:02:58.879 --> 00:03:01.269
Albert traveled all across France and Europe

00:03:01.269 --> 00:03:05.128
buying things in small quantities to leave&nbsp;no obvious trace. &nbsp;

00:03:05.128 --> 00:03:08.629
The idea was that all of the&nbsp;equipment 
left behind after the heist

00:03:08.629 --> 00:03:11.177
would lead&nbsp;the police on a wild goose chase, 

00:03:11.177 --> 00:03:14.323
one that would&nbsp;ultimately lead them nowhere. &nbsp;

00:03:14.323 --> 00:03:15.256
With everything&nbsp;bought

00:03:15.256 --> 00:03:17.757
the sewer rats could now start digging.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:18.720 --> 00:03:21.172
Some of the team entered the sewers via the ramp&nbsp;

00:03:21.172 --> 00:03:24.240
and drove over a mile to reach the sewage tunnel.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:24.240 --> 00:03:26.359
From there, they had to walk around 300 m 

00:03:26.359 --> 00:03:28.715
to reach the crucial digging point. 

00:03:28.715 --> 00:03:30.282
The rest of the gang entered the sewers&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:30.282 --> 00:03:33.458
 through an access room&nbsp;in an underground parking garage. 

00:03:33.458 --> 00:03:34.080
From there

00:03:34.080 --> 00:03:36.332
the crew ran an enormous electrical cable 

00:03:36.332 --> 00:03:39.600
from the&nbsp;outlet in the parking garage down into the sewers,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:39.600 --> 00:03:42.256
giving them power for lights and tools. 

00:03:42.256 --> 00:03:45.280
Like&nbsp;a well-oiled machine, they started drilling,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:46.518
removing tons of rock

00:03:46.518 --> 00:03:49.753
 and piling it up&nbsp;in an unused part of the sewer. 

00:03:49.753 --> 00:03:52.743
To avoid&nbsp;any suspicion from the town's sewage workers,&nbsp;

00:03:52.743 --> 00:03:54.720
they cemented up the entrance of their tunnel&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:54.720 --> 00:03:57.946
to make it look identical to the other tunnel&nbsp;entrances. 

00:03:57.946 --> 00:03:59.280
Once they were done for the night,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:05.112
they'd leave all of their equipment covered&nbsp;up inside 
a hole in the tunnel and quietly&nbsp;make their way out. 

00:04:05.112 --> 00:04:06.310
For 2 months, 

00:04:06.310 --> 00:04:07.855
the team went&nbsp;down into the sewers 

00:04:07.855 --> 00:04:09.600
and worked on their tunnel.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:09.600 --> 00:04:11.750
Many of the crew were above ground on lookout&nbsp;

00:04:11.750 --> 00:04:13.840
with radios that allowed them to warn the crew&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:13.840 --> 00:04:16.119
if anyone was entering the sewers. 

00:04:16.119 --> 00:04:18.386
The whole&nbsp;operation was so professional

00:04:18.386 --> 00:04:20.531
 and after 2&nbsp;months of straight digging, 

00:04:20.531 --> 00:04:22.954
they knew they had&nbsp;to be getting close. 

00:04:22.954 --> 00:04:25.200
Then one night in July

00:04:25.200 --> 00:04:28.701
the crew finally hit the concrete walls of the&nbsp;vault

00:04:28.701 --> 00:04:31.224
but the timing was terrible. 

00:04:31.224 --> 00:04:32.080
That weekend,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:32.080 --> 00:04:35.386
the president of France had made a last minute&nbsp;visit to Nice

00:04:35.386 --> 00:04:38.621
and there were enormous amounts&nbsp;
of police and security in the city.

00:04:38.621 --> 00:04:41.764
It was not&nbsp;the time to be robbing a bank. &nbsp;

00:04:41.764 --> 00:04:44.910
Albert decided to&nbsp;call off the heist until the following weekend

00:04:44.910 --> 00:04:47.066
which was a holiday weekend.

00:04:47.066 --> 00:04:48.900
 This meant that&nbsp;the bank would be closed, 

00:04:48.900 --> 00:04:50.697
giving the crew more&nbsp;time to break in 

00:04:50.697 --> 00:04:53.120
and get as much as possible.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:54.033
In the meantime, 

00:04:54.033 --> 00:04:56.856
Albert had some other matters to&nbsp;attend to.

00:04:56.856 --> 00:04:58.480
Since he was the mayor's photographer,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:58.480 --> 00:05:01.461
he was actually a guest at the president's&nbsp;event. 

00:05:01.461 --> 00:05:03.840
Just hours before this picture was taken,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:03.840 --> 00:05:05.589
Albert was down in the tunnel 

00:05:05.589 --> 00:05:08.735
digging his way to the city's biggest bank. &nbsp;

00:05:08.735 --> 00:05:11.770
He was managing the&nbsp;whole operation incredibly well

00:05:11.770 --> 00:05:14.359
and it was all&nbsp;thanks to Odoo. 

