00:06:23.665 --> 00:06:26.706
It's Saturday, the&nbsp;17th of July. 

00:06:26.706 --> 00:06:30.000
After hours of chipping away at the&nbsp;reinforced concrete,

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:34.000
the sewer rats now had their&nbsp;first glimpse inside the vault. 

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:36.301
The bank would be&nbsp;opening up on Monday morning, 

00:06:36.301 --> 00:06:39.186
so the crew had just&nbsp;over 30 hours to get in, 

00:06:39.186 --> 00:06:40.720
take as much as possible,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:40.720 --> 00:06:43.786
and leave through the sewers without getting&nbsp;caught. 

00:06:43.786 --> 00:06:44.720
Later that evening, 

00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:48.755
the hole was finally&nbsp;big enough for the gang to enter the vault. &nbsp;

00:06:48.755 --> 00:06:53.040
After&nbsp;months of digging, it was time to start the heist.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:53.040 --> 00:06:55.251
Over the next 30 hours, 

00:06:55.251 --> 00:06:58.652
the gang went crazy,&nbsp;prying open the safe deposit boxes 

00:06:58.652 --> 00:07:00.876
and taking as&nbsp;much as they could. 

00:07:00.876 --> 00:07:02.162
They found everything.

00:07:02.162 --> 00:07:05.985
Stacks&nbsp;of gold bars, cash, jewels, stock certificates,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:05.985 --> 00:07:09.151
and even some saucy photographs of high&nbsp;up politicians, 

00:07:09.151 --> 00:07:12.052
which the crew hung on&nbsp;the walls of the tunnel. &nbsp;

00:07:12.052 --> 00:07:13.416
After 30 hours, 

00:07:13.416 --> 00:07:16.640
the crew&nbsp;finally took a break, had dinner inside the vault,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:16.640 --> 00:07:19.309
and celebrated with bottles of red wine. 

00:07:19.309 --> 00:07:22.800
But time&nbsp;was almost up, and at 5:00 AM on Monday morning,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:22.800 --> 00:07:25.754
they packed up the last bit of treasure and left&nbsp;the vault,

00:07:25.754 --> 00:07:29.044
 leaving behind one final message on the&nbsp;wall. 

00:07:29.044 --> 00:07:31.349
They loaded the stash into the getaway car&nbsp;

00:07:31.349 --> 00:07:35.000
and disappeared into the city just before sunrise.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:37.429
A few hours later, at 8:00 AM,

00:07:37.429 --> 00:07:39.829
the bank was&nbsp;getting ready to open. 

00:07:39.829 --> 00:07:42.041
One of the workers went to open the vault door,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:42.041 --> 00:07:45.288
 but surprisingly, it didn't&nbsp;move. 

00:07:45.288 --> 00:07:47.600
The lock mechanism was working perfectly,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:47.600 --> 00:07:50.096
but the door just would not open. 

00:07:50.096 --> 00:07:53.120
As it turned&nbsp;out, just before the crew had left the vault,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:53.120 --> 00:07:55.000
they had welded the door shut, 

00:07:55.000 --> 00:07:57.000
buying them some&nbsp;extra time. 

00:07:57.000 --> 00:07:59.289
After several hours of confusion,&nbsp;

00:07:59.289 --> 00:08:02.157
the bank decided to drill their way into the vault.&nbsp;

00:08:02.157 --> 00:08:05.224
And only then was it obvious what had happened.

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:15.000
It might seem like the police had a lot of&nbsp;evidence. 

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:18.646
Equipment had been littered across&nbsp;the vault and in the sewers. &nbsp;

00:08:18.646 --> 00:08:21.617
Surely something&nbsp;would lead to one of the thieves. 

00:08:21.617 --> 00:08:22.640
But amazingly,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:22.640 --> 00:08:25.167
not a single fingerprint was found. &nbsp;

00:08:25.167 --> 00:08:28.234
The crew&nbsp;had worn gloves the entire time. 

00:08:28.234 --> 00:08:30.757
Even the&nbsp;urine came back with no results

00:08:30.757 --> 00:08:34.480
since multiple&nbsp;people had urinated in every single bottle.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:34.480 --> 00:08:37.581
Albert and his crew had thought of everything.

00:08:37.581 --> 00:08:38.958
But&nbsp;what he didn't know 

00:08:38.958 --> 00:08:41.272
was that the events that would lead to his arrest&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:41.272 --> 00:08:45.279
had already taken place 2 weeks&nbsp;before the heist. 

00:08:45.279 --> 00:08:46.424
Up in the mountains, &nbsp;

00:08:46.424 --> 00:08:48.414
the police&nbsp;were called to a villa. 

00:08:48.414 --> 00:08:50.510
Normally, this villa was&nbsp;empty, 

00:08:50.510 --> 00:08:53.223
but the neighbor had seen a suspicious&nbsp;group of men&nbsp;

00:08:53.223 --> 00:08:56.159
constantly leaving and entering&nbsp;the villa. 

00:08:56.159 --> 00:08:57.760
When the police questioned the men,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:08:57.760 --> 00:09:00.132
they simply said that they had permission from the&nbsp;owner 

00:09:00.132 --> 00:09:01.621
to use the villa. 

00:09:01.621 --> 00:09:03.200
Something wasn't right,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:03.200 --> 00:09:05.283
but there was nothing more the police could do. &nbsp;

00:09:05.283 --> 00:09:08.117
So&nbsp;they took down the names of the men and left. &nbsp;

00:09:08.117 --> 00:09:11.550
But when the heist later became
 headline news all over&nbsp;the country, 

00:09:11.550 --> 00:09:13.549
the police officers couldn't shake&nbsp;their suspicion&nbsp;

00:09:13.549 --> 00:09:16.586
 that the villa had something to do&nbsp;with the heist. 

00:09:16.586 --> 00:09:20.421
And so they got a search warrant and returned to the villa. &nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:20.421 --> 00:09:23.849
After 100 days of the&nbsp;investigation leading nowhere, 

00:09:23.849 --> 00:09:26.572
they were about to&nbsp;get their first clue. &nbsp;

00:09:26.572 --> 00:09:27.727
Inside the villa, 

00:09:27.727 --> 00:09:31.284
the place&nbsp;was full of tools, equipment, and dirty clothes,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:31.284 --> 00:09:34.612
all identical to those found in the sewers. 

00:09:34.612 --> 00:09:36.056
Two&nbsp;of the men from the villa, 

00:09:36.056 --> 00:09:38.347
Alain Bournat and Francis&nbsp;Pellegrin

00:09:38.347 --> 00:09:39.438
were arrested 

00:09:39.438 --> 00:09:42.728
and almost immediately,&nbsp;they told the police everything, 

00:09:42.728 --> 00:09:44.463
even naming&nbsp;Albert Spaggiari

00:09:44.463 --> 00:09:47.475
as the mastermind behind the whole&nbsp;thing. 

00:09:47.475 --> 00:09:50.000
The police were finally getting somewhere.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:53.362
Now they had to find their biggest target. 

00:09:53.362 --> 00:09:56.674
But&nbsp;Albert was gone. &nbsp;&nbsp;

00:09:56.674 --> 00:09:58.720
Just a few days after the heist,

00:09:58.720 --> 00:09:59.784
he fled the country &nbsp;

00:09:59.784 --> 00:10:04.019
and spent the next 2 months&nbsp;
traveling through Guatemala and the US. 

00:10:04.019 --> 00:10:07.390
When he was there, he even made a phone call to the CIA

00:10:07.390 --> 00:10:10.768
and admitted to being the mastermind behind the&nbsp;heist. 

00:10:10.768 --> 00:10:12.260
He was getting overconfident 

00:10:12.260 --> 00:10:16.129
and eventually returned to Nice and continued living his life.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:16.129 --> 00:10:19.593
Then one morning, while having lunch with his wife&nbsp;in a cafe, 

00:10:19.593 --> 00:10:22.272
Albert was approached by the waitress.

00:10:29.520 --> 00:10:33.953
When he walked out, he was instantly&nbsp;
surrounded by police officers and arrested.

00:10:40.244 --> 00:10:42.666
Over the next 36 hours, &nbsp;

00:10:42.666 --> 00:10:44.800
the&nbsp;police interrogated Albert

00:10:44.800 --> 00:10:47.937
but he refused to give them any&nbsp;information. &nbsp;

00:10:47.937 --> 00:10:49.805
It wasn't until his&nbsp;first court appearance 

00:10:49.805 --> 00:10:52.217
that he finally&nbsp;started to talk.

00:11:16.884 --> 00:11:20.000
Very little of what Albert said in court&nbsp;was accurate. 

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:21.389
He was just playing with the&nbsp;police

00:11:21.389 --> 00:11:23.688
and wasting the judge's time. 

00:11:23.688 --> 00:11:26.711
Over&nbsp;the winter, Albert went to court every&nbsp;week&nbsp;

00:11:26.711 --> 00:11:30.306
and continued to give vague and inaccurate&nbsp;information. 

00:11:30.306 --> 00:11:32.129
But on his 20th visit to the court,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:32.129 --> 00:11:34.746
things would go a bit differently.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:34.746 --> 00:11:37.858
As always, Albert was taken up to the&nbsp;judge's office

00:11:37.858 --> 00:11:40.915
where the police uncuffed&nbsp;him and locked the doors. 

00:11:40.915 --> 00:11:41.760
The week before,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:43.065
Albert had promised the judge 

00:11:43.065 --> 00:11:45.065
that he would&nbsp;give him a detailed description &nbsp;

00:11:45.065 --> 00:11:47.166
of how the&nbsp;heist went down. 

00:11:47.166 --> 00:11:49.366
And so, Albert pulled out a&nbsp;piece of paper 

00:11:49.366 --> 00:11:51.366
and put it on the judge's desk.

00:12:04.289 --> 00:12:06.798
Suddenly, Albert ran to the nearest window, 

00:12:06.798 --> 00:12:08.798
threw&nbsp;it open, and jumped out. 

00:12:08.798 --> 00:12:10.000
He landed on a ledge,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:10.000 --> 00:12:12.453
rolled, and jumped onto a car that was&nbsp;parked below, 

00:12:12.453 --> 00:12:14.609
making a giant dent in the&nbsp;roof.

00:12:14.609 --> 00:12:18.417
Right beside the car was a motorbike 
with&nbsp;the rider revving its engine.

00:12:18.417 --> 00:12:19.440
Albert hopped on,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:19.440 --> 00:12:22.812
and in just a matter of seconds, he was gone.&nbsp;

00:12:22.812 --> 00:12:26.857
The French borders were closed 
and all flights&nbsp;leaving the country were cancelled

00:12:26.857 --> 00:12:28.474
but it was&nbsp;too late. 

00:12:28.474 --> 00:12:31.185
Albert had vanished. &nbsp;

00:12:31.185 --> 00:12:31.920
As it turned out,&nbsp;

00:12:31.920 --> 00:12:34.247
Albert had fled to South America.

00:12:34.247 --> 00:12:36.958
And with the help&nbsp;of plastic surgery and a wig, 

00:12:36.958 --> 00:12:39.827
he was now living in&nbsp;disguise. 

00:12:39.827 --> 00:12:41.212
A few months after his escape, 

00:12:41.212 --> 00:12:44.080
he sent&nbsp;a picture of himself to a local newspaper saying,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:44.080 --> 00:12:45.968
"Greetings from Albert." 

00:12:45.968 --> 00:12:48.213
He even sent&nbsp;the owner of the car that he damaged,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:48.213 --> 00:12:51.309
$600, and an apology note.

00:12:51.309 --> 00:12:54.800
 In France, the&nbsp;courts had sentenced him to life in prison,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:54.800 --> 00:12:56.994
but he still managed to come back every now and&nbsp;then 

00:12:56.994 --> 00:12:59.473
and visit his mom and his wife.

00:12:59.473 --> 00:13:00.240
 In the end,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:00.240 --> 00:13:01.923
just four men were convicted 

00:13:01.923 --> 00:13:05.101
and only&nbsp;served about 6 months in jail. 

00:13:05.101 --> 00:13:08.037
Albert lived the rest of his life as a free man&nbsp;

00:13:08.037 --> 00:13:11.544
until he eventually died of cancer in 1989.

